<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idee3af2ce-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s499q"><num value="499q">§ 499q.</num><heading> Separability</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If any provision of this chapter or the application thereof to any person or circumstances is held invalid, the validity of the remainder of the chapter and of the application of such provision to other persons and circumstances shall not be affected thereby.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idee3af2cf-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1930-06-10/ch436/s17">June 10, 1930, ch. 436, § 17</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/46/538">46 Stat. 538</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idee3af2d0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idee3af2d1-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idee3af2d2-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s567">section 567 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
